<P><H5><U><B>What to do next</B></U></H5><P>
<p>We recommend opening the output CIF file in <a class="reference" href="reel.htm">REEL</a> to make sure
that the results are what you expect.  The CIF may be used in any applications
requiring restraints as input (primarily <a class="reference" href="refine_gui.htm">phenix.refine</a>,
the <a class="reference" href="validation.htm">validation tools</a>, and the <a class="reference" href="autobuild.htm">AutoBuild</a>
and <a class="reference" href="ligandfit_gui.htm">LigandFit</a> wizards).  If you have not already
placed your ligand in the model, the PDB file is suitable for this, but we
recommend trying LigandFit first to save time.</p>
